{"type": "article", "id": 56900, "title": "一款咖啡机，能把冷萃的制作时间压缩至四分钟｜这个设计了不起", "description": "我们每天都为你推荐几个最近发现的好设计。", "date": "2018-09-28T23:13:41Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 271, "name": "工业设计"}, {"id": 768, "name": "产品设计"}, {"id": 42213, "name": "Lendager Group"}, {"id": 14337, "name": "Reform"}, {"id": 53095, "name": "Yield"}, {"id": 53096, "name": "Asa Pingree"}, {"id": 53097, "name": "Jesper Eriksson"}, {"id": 53098, "name": "Eduardo Umaña"}], "category": 17, "column": 38, "author": 1329, "comment_count": 8, "praise_count": 153, "image": "img/article/article_show/20180928215828wmOxJzAlK6LbpCDo.gif", "contents": "<p nocleanhtml=\"true\">        <style type=\"text/css\"> p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 11.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #000000; -webkit-text-stroke: #000000} p.p2 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 11.0px Helvetica; color: #000000; -webkit-text-stroke: #000000} p.p3 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 18.0px; font: 16.2px Arial; color: #444444; -webkit-text-stroke: #444444; background-color: #ffffff; min-height: 19.0px} span.s1 {font-kerning: none} span.s2 {font: 11.0px Helvetica; font-kerning: none} span.s3 {text-decoration: underline ; font-kerning: none} span.s4 {font: 11.0px 'PingFang SC'; font-kerning: none} </style>  </p><p>「这个设计了不起」的微信公众号上线啦，直接搜索「BestDesign」或是「Qthings」就可以订阅，关注我们每日发现的新鲜好设计。</p><h3>FrankOne by Eduardo Umaña</h3><p>冷萃咖啡是不少咖啡爱好者的心头好，它是用冷水浸泡咖啡粉 12 小时以上进行萃取再过滤，类似冷泡茶的做法。但想要喝到地道的冷萃咖啡，就要耐心等待它慢慢萃取的过程。</p><p>最近，众筹平台 Kickstarter 上线了一款名为 FrankOne 的咖啡机，能够加速冷萃咖啡的萃取过程，仅需 4 分钟即可。与其它的手工萃取方式不同的是，FrankOne 的真空抽吸技术利用负压力迫使水通过咖啡粉，可以提取咖啡所蕴含的更多样的味道，同时减少苦味。</p><p>它的专利方法能产生足够强的压力，使你的咖啡粉的研磨尺寸可以从细到粗自由切换。不同的研磨尺寸意味着可以酿造出各种各样的作品，从普通咖啡到冷萃，想冷就冷想热就热，一台 FrankOne 就可以搞定。</p><p>在耗电量方面，FrankOne 仅需 2 小时即可通过 USB 充满电，一次充电可以制作 150 次咖啡。早鸟价 70 美元，<a href=\"https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/edumana/frankone-the-first-one-touch-specialty-coffee-brew?ref=btonos\" rel=\"nofollow\">点击这里尝试预购</a>。</p><div class=\"com-insert-embed com-insert-embeds\">\r\n\t<figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n\t\t<iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"https://v.qq.com/txp/iframe/player.html?vid=n0722j8aen4\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></iframe>\r\n\t</figure>\r\n\t\r\n</div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201809282159132oHNY4lsiZRf6Art.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/2018092821591387W1JyzKvXZOpF0t.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928215913e7GMU5YsuHT3vJBD.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928215915vH97D1CAXJUYEzTa.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.562791\" data-format=\"gif\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>A Broad Set of Furniture and Household Goods by Yield </h3><p>佛罗里达设计工作室 Yield 推出了一系列家具和家居用品新品。创始人 Andrew Deming 和 Rachel Gant 的目标，是尽可能在当地生产他们的产品。</p><p>最新系列包括 Duotone 桌子，由精密加工的实心黄铜制成，桌子设有两层架子，有矩形、方形和圆形，所有桌子均在圣奥古斯丁制造。Aurora 桌子采用回收材料制成，形成十字形交叉弯曲底座，搭配一块椭圆形的透明烟熏色或者青铜色玻璃桌面。</p><p>双层耐热玻璃杯和法压壶则是使用在中国生产的硼硅酸盐玻璃制成，配有铜质拉杆。此外，这个系列还包括花盆、烛台等。售价 80 美元起，<a href=\"https://yielddesign.co/collections/home\" rel=\"nofollow\">点击这里尝试购买</a>。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928215956EW5xgiVrBemN9KJ8.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.562793\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928215956A5yS7Yset49vimN8.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928215957KQCE3ruYBDjRSonl.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928215957mi9aWYO2otq6CTf3.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928215957faBgjTNwr5eq8IUJ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928215959lOpVz9rdERgjIuek.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><h3>Making Marble From Coal by Jesper Eriksson</h3><p>伦敦艺术家、设计师 Jesper Eriksson 探索煤炭材料的应用，创造了一系列家具。作为英国工业革命的代名词，煤炭被视为一种功能齐全的原材料，它的价值完全来自于燃烧后所能供给的能量。</p><p>但 Jesper Eriksson 想要将其用作制造材料，制作地板、家具和其他物品，其中一些碎片保留了材料的原始状态，而其他物品则加工成类似于黑色大理石的饰面。</p><p>Making Marble From Coal 项目是今年伦敦设计双年展的一部分。英国政府已宣布他们将在 2025 年停止燃煤能源生产，Jesper Eriksson 担心这将影响集体记忆的消逝。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201809282200364WteuzJ2mqKQwMCk.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667482\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928220036n4FXTkaBMuRiWGhm.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667482\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928220036hRmusl2YgrJKBAv3.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667482\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928220039PHbIitN3R5jWYTmD.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667482\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/2018092822003972E9UXZwlu5zxWvT.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667482\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201809282200391lfmIqVNhS9XaA6d.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.001222\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/2018092822003948movWI75iQsJctr.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.036675\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928220039PHJg6EkeyKbR3ft4.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.497555\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\">图片来源：<a href=\"https://www.designboom.com/design/jesper-eriksson-post-fuel-coal-design-09-27-2018/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Designboom</a></figcaption></figure></div><h3>UP Minimalist Kitchen by Lendager Group</h3><p>UP 是由 Lendager Group 为丹麦公司 Reform 设计的全新极简主义厨房，采用来自知名地板制造商 Dinesen 的木材。自创立以来，创始人一直希望提供可持续的厨房设计。</p><p>丹麦公司 Reform 算是比较特别的一家，它的业务重点放在为宜家量身定制整体式厨房。这同样是一家与宜家相似，坚持简洁审美的公司，改造手法也与很多宜家骇客们追求标新立异的理念不同，是在尝试为基础感创造更多能够融入日常生活且持久耐看的好设计。</p><p>与 Dinesen 的合作，使得他们获得了使用 Dinesen 废弃木材的独家权利，试图为这些木材碎片赋予新生命。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928220125JG0Le5PVjlpiEy9q.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666400\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928220125fSJcI6X3vjAUksxl.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.333600\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928220126oSxA43Izv1MZe69f.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.333600\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201809282201257dTBrX218G9kReEF.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.500000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928220126xBEkDU3zvjLmSr47.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.500000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201809282201277Vv5ljx19tFgWaOI.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.333600\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928220129kGM7g6AaDNv2Y8uT.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.477600\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\">图片来源：<a href=\"https://www.reformcph.com/en/design/up-lendager-group/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Reform</a></figcaption></figure></div><h3>A Playful Exploration with Fiberglass by Asa Pingree</h3><p>当你想到玻璃纤维时，你可能会联想到标志性的 Eames 夫妇设计的模压玻璃纤维椅子，但设计师 Asa Pingree 表明，这种材料的应用可能性其实还很广阔，可以形成很多形状。</p><p>Asa Pingree 推出的新玻璃纤维系列，灵感来自于他作为缅因州海岸岛屿上造船工人的儿子的记忆。在设计休闲椅、长凳、脚凳和沙发床时，Pingree 探索了形状和平衡之间的关系，使得每件产品看上去都坚固且轻盈。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201809282202160aIxuGZHn7XCzKbf.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666406\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928220217zt7yjUxBfXrWacDY.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.239844\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928220216Vgi2KBohU6CqWm7S.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.240625\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928220216qFOkRXnCVSt18vTo.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.225000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928220218S9JG2pxUbumYOsvc.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.332212\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928220218IBafxj9Z6po4lAEt.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.634375\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928220219O4ZlnwiFGjdkeWVs.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.239933\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20180928220219EOWsJdSe3cr9lAqR.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.239933\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\r\n<figcaption class=\"\">图片来源：<a href=\"http://asapingree.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Asa Pingree</a></figcaption></figure></div><p class=\"\"><br></p>"}